ntioned partnering with orders of government to further support vulnerable Canadians during the pandemic.&#10;3. Language interpretation services are being utilized to ensure all parliament members can understand the proceedings. In this transcript, a point of order was raised by Mr. Jol Godin regarding his inability to hear the French interpretation of the Prime Minister's speech.&#10;4. Although no direct actions related to pandemic shutdowns in First Nations communities like La Loche were mentioned, Hon. Marc Miller acknowledged that overcrowded housing and lack of healthcare infrastructure make Indigenous communities more vulnerable during the pandemic, and they are working on addressing these issues by deploying measures such as surge capacity, increased PPE, and medical personnel.">
