e that the Liberal government's approach to firearms legislation and regulation is misguided. They point out numerous inaccuracies about current firearms legislation and regulation, and the use of the term &quot;military-style assault rifles&quot; is a political phrase undefined in Canadian law. They also note that municipalities are constitutionally unable to enact criminal law to ban handguns in their jurisdictions.&#10;4. Moreover, experts agree that banning firearms and adding unnecessary red tape will not increase public safety. The majority of guns used in violent crimes are smuggled into Canada from the United States. Therefore, the government should focus its limited resources on anti-gang enforcement, reducing the involvement of at-risk youth and gangs, mental health, and other relevant issues rather than targeting law-abiding firearms owners.">
