rance, where governments have taken action against companies using tax havens or made such practices ineligible for public assistance. The Canadian government has been urged to show leadership and make regulatory amendments to prevent the abuse of tax havens by companies.&#10;&#10;In summary, although the government has taken steps to combat tax evasion, it has not yet addressed the issue of legal tax avoidance strategies employed by corporations using tax havens. There is an ongoing debate in Parliament regarding the need for regulatory amendments to prevent such practices, especially in light of financial institutions saving billions through these mechanisms while receiving government assistance during the COVID-19 pandemic.">
